column2: No information whatsoever can be inferred from this exceptional value (e.g, unknown if the patient had a first recurrence)
No proper value is applicable in this context (e.g., patient became disease-free after treatment; never had a recurrence; or patient was never disease-free; autopsy only case)
A proper value is appicable but not known (i.e., there was a recurrence, but the date is unknown)
A valid date value is provided in item Recurrence Date--1st [1860], or the date was not expected to have been transmitted
